Product name: 14k Gold Pansy Ring | Blue Enamel Pansy Ring | Vintage Pin Conversion Ring | 14k Gold Ring | Pansy Flower Ring
Description:
Shakespeare referred to pansies as "Cupid's flower."  In a Midsummer Night's Dream, Oberon and Puck schemed to put drops of pansy juice in a sleeping Demetrius' eyes to make him fall in love with the first woman he saw upon waking.
This lovely ring features a finely enameled blue pansy of 14k gold with a pearl center on a 14k gold band. The flower on this ring was originally part of a vintage pin (circa 1960) that we converted into a ring.
The pansy measures measures 0.6 inches (14mm) tall by 0.6 inches (14mm) wide and the condition is excellent.
The ring is currently a size 6.5, but it can be re-sized free of charge.

So a book for M-A-T-T-H-E-W would have a different story to a book for O-L-I-V-E.

Care and cleaning:
Machine wash warm – you can periodically use hot water for extra sanitation. Do not use fabric softeners or other additives. Wash inside out. After laundering line dry or machine dry on low. In addition the waterproof surface can be easily wiped clean with a wet cloth. (Source: http://www.babyvilleboutique.com)
To seal the seams of the wet bag, wash before using and dry on high heat for 20 minutes (only the first time). After in initial wash and dry, wash and dry as normal.
The wet bags can be made in any PUL pattern. If you would like a different pattern than pictured, please specify the PUL style in the comments section.
